The paper deals with the automated synthesis of digital controllers for dynamical plants, which is a topic that falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of counterexample guided inductive synthesis, which is a technique commonly used in program synthesis (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the effects of quantization and finite-precision arithmetic, which are topics related to optimization (cs.LO), robotics (cs.RO), and software engineering (cs.SE).
